### 🐛 BUG DETECTED:

**Bug: Pre-loaded code blocks do NOT show syntax highlighting on initial page load**

- **Story**: Editor > Code
- **Behavior**: When the "Code" story loads with pre-existing HTML code content, the code block is rendered with **NO syntax highlighting** - all text appears in the same uniform dark color
- **Expected**: The pre-loaded code should display proper syntax highlighting immediately upon page load
- **Actual**: All HTML tags, attributes, and content text are displayed in the same color with no differentiation
- **Workaround**: Clicking/focusing the editor triggers the syntax highlighting to appear
- **Impact**: This is a rendering/initialization bug - the syntax highlighter is not applied to pre-existing code blocks during initial render, only activated after user interaction (focus event)
